The paper deals with signal detection in optical wireless communication, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of photomultiplier tubes (PMT) and sampling also involves optics and hardware (cs.OH) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the receiver, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY).
